    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/146.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Canada</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 8. Inform Carranza United States Government protests earnestly
                    against applying to Americans and other foreigners <pb facs="0988" n="872"
                        xml:id="pg_872"/> decree suspending operation oil wells. Advise him serious
                    complications and consequences will result if the right assumed of destroying
                    property belonging to them is carried into effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
